com.cs371group2

Class Dao<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cs371group2.Dao<E>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcernDao

    public abstract class Dao<E>
extends Object
    Generic data access object for loading, saving, and deleting entities from the datastore. This class should be subclassed for every entity that is stored in the database. Created on 2017-01-19.

      • save

        public com.googlecode.objectify.Key<E> save(E entity)
        Saves an entity of type E synchronously to the datastore. If an entity with the same identifier already exists it will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity to be saved to the datastore.
        Returns:
        The key used to load the entity from the datastore.
        Pre-condition:
        entity != null
        Post-condition:
        The entity has been saved to the datastore for future loading and / or deleting. If the entity has an identifier of type long it will have been populated with the entity's unique identifier.

      • delete

        public com.googlecode.objectify.Result<Void> delete(E entity)
        Deletes an entity of type E from the datastore.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity to be deleted.
        Pre-condition:
        entity != null
        Post-condition:
        The entity is no longer present in the datastore.
